are what we call RBI Circulars.

00:00:37.920 --> 00:00:43.140
They are basically official memos, or you
can say WhatsApp forwards from the family

00:00:43.140 --> 00:00:46.050
head that everyone must read and follow.

00:00:46.500 --> 00:00:51.300
They serve as updates, new rules
or clarifications, ensuring all

00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:55.500
financial players are on the same
page, operating safely and working

00:00:55.500 --> 00:00:57.600
towards our national economic goals.

00:00:58.025 --> 00:01:02.525
These circulars can be about anything
from interest rates and lending rules

00:01:02.615 --> 00:01:07.475
to digital payment, safety, and customer
service, all to maintain the stability

00:01:07.475 --> 00:01:10.115
and integrity of our financial system.

00:01:10.505 --> 00:01:11.885
Real world relevance.

00:01:12.275 --> 00:01:16.775
Understanding these circulars is
absolutely critical because they

00:01:16.775 --> 00:01:20.765
directly hit banking operations,
making sure banks are compliant and

00:01:20.765 --> 00:01:22.685
implementing regulations properly.

00:01:23.110 --> 00:01:27.940
This knowledge helps in managing risks,
improving customer service, and making

00:01:27.940 --> 00:01:30.095
smart strategic decisions within the bank.

00:01:30.855 --> 00:01:33.495
Now these circulars come in many flavors.

00:01:33.825 --> 00:01:37.905
There are six important categories
you should know first, monetary

00:01:37.905 --> 00:01:41.775
policy circulars, which are
directives on big rates like repo

00:01:41.775 --> 00:01:44.835
rate, reverse repo rate, CRR and SLR.

00:01:45.255 --> 00:01:48.645
Then we have prudential norms,
which are guidelines on asset

00:01:48.645 --> 00:01:51.015
classification and capital adequacy.

00:01:51.414 --> 00:01:55.405
Next, our customer service and
protection rules covering grievances

00:01:55.405 --> 00:01:56.964
and digital banking safety.

00:01:57.414 --> 00:02:00.774
We also have foreign exchange
management for all things

00:02:00.774 --> 00:02:02.244
related to foreign currency.

00:02:02.634 --> 00:02:07.914
Then there's financial inclusion, which
pushes banking services to unbanked areas.

00:02:08.245 --> 00:02:12.234
And finally, digital banking
and payments with guidelines on

00:02:12.234 --> 00:02:15.775
U-P-I-N-E-F-T-R-T-G-S and cybersecurity.

