First, identify the issuer and recipient
who sent it, and who is it for?

00:04:09.395 --> 00:04:12.425
Is it for all commercial
banks or just N BFCs?

00:04:12.755 --> 00:04:15.215
Second, read the subject line carefully.

00:04:15.365 --> 00:04:17.915
It's the trailer of the movie,
giving you a quick summary.

00:04:18.894 --> 00:04:23.455
Third, understand the background circulars
often refer to older ones, and knowing

00:04:23.455 --> 00:04:25.555
the history helps you see the big picture.

00:04:25.735 --> 00:04:27.925
Fourth, pinpoint the core directive.

00:04:28.105 --> 00:04:31.645
What is the RBI actually
asking banks to do or not To?

00:04:31.945 --> 00:04:33.805
Fifth note, key definitions.

00:04:33.955 --> 00:04:37.945
If a new term is introduced, pay
close attention to its exact meaning.

00:04:38.185 --> 00:04:41.005
Sixth, look for effective
dates and deadlines.

00:04:41.125 --> 00:04:42.240
When do the rules kick in?

