00:05:19.859 --> 00:05:21.929
Common mistakes and misconceptions.

00:05:22.200 --> 00:05:24.450
Now, let's talk about the common traps.

00:05:24.659 --> 00:05:29.130
A big one is confusing dates, mixing up
the issue date with the effective date.

00:05:29.460 --> 00:05:33.450
Another is incorrect applicability,
assuming a rule for commercial

00:05:33.450 --> 00:05:35.155
banks also applies to n BFCs.

00:05:35.885 --> 00:05:38.945
Relying on outdated information
is a classic blunder.

00:05:39.185 --> 00:05:43.835
RBI updates things frequently, so always
look for the latest master directions.

00:05:44.224 --> 00:05:47.495
Many friends also stumble by
misinterpreting terminology

00:05:47.614 --> 00:05:50.224
and not knowing the precise
legal meaning of terms.

00:05:50.525 --> 00:05:54.065
And finally, ignoring amendments
is a recipe for disaster.

00:05:54.304 --> 00:05:57.515
Always check if a circular
has been updated or replaced.

